---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="The Performance Decay Cycle | Fast by Default"
  description="The Performance Decay Cycle is a pattern identified by Den Odell where teams ship fast, accumulate performance debt, panic-fix, and repeat. Fast by Default breaks this loop."
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-stone-50 dark:bg-stone-950">
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <div
      class="border-b-4 border-double border-stone-900 dark:border-stone-100 bg-white dark:bg-stone-900"
    >
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
        <div class="text-center">
          <a
            href="/"
            class="inline-block text-xs font-sans tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400 mb-4 hover:text-stone-700 dark:hover:text-stone-200 transition-colors"
          >
            &larr; Fast by Default
          </a>
          <h1
            class="font-display text-5xl sm:text-7xl font-black text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-50 tracking-tight mb-6"
          >
            The Performance Decay Cycle
          </h1>
          <p
            class="text-xl text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto"
          >
            The Performance Decay Cycle is a pattern, identified by <a
              href="https://denodell.com"
              class="text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-200 underline hover:text-stone-600 dark:hover:text-stone-400 transition-colors"
              >Den Odell</a
            >, where teams ship fast, accumulate performance debt, panic-fix,
            and repeat. Fast by Default breaks this loop.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Content -->
    <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
      <p
        class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-stone-800 dark:text-stone-200 mb-12"
      >
        Most teams do not become slow overnight. They follow a predictable loop
        that feels productive but creates long-term drag. This cycle is so
        common that nearly every engineering organization has experienced it at
        some point.
      </p>

      <!-- The Cycle Diagram -->
      <div class="my-12 flex justify-center">
        <!-- Light Mode SVG -->
        <svg
          width="500"
          height="500"
          viewBox="0 0 500 500"
          class="max-w-full h-auto dark:hidden"
        >
          <!-- Center circle -->
          <circle
            cx="250"
            cy="250"
            r="55"
            fill="#fafaf9"
            stroke="#78716c"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-dasharray="4 2"></circle>
          <text
            x="250"
            y="245"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="12"
            fill="#78716c">Performance</text
          >
          <text
            x="250"
            y="260"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="12"
            fill="#78716c">Decay</text
          >

          <!-- Node 1: Ship (top) -->
          <circle
            cx="250"
            cy="70"
            r="50"
            fill="#78716c"
            stroke="#57534e"
            stroke-width="2"></circle>
          <text
            x="250"
            y="75"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="14"
            font-weight="bold"
            fill="white">Ship</text
          >

          <!-- Node 2: Complain (top right) -->
          <circle
            cx="400"
            cy="160"
            r="50"
            fill="#78716c"
            stroke="#57534e"
            stroke-width="2"></circle>
          <text
            x="400"
            y="165"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="14"
            font-weight="bold"
            fill="white">Complain</text
          >

          <!-- Node 3: Panic (bottom right) -->
          <circle
            cx="370"
            cy="360"
            r="50"
            fill="#78716c"
            stroke="#57534e"
            stroke-width="2"></circle>
          <text
            x="370"
            y="365"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="14"
            font-weight="bold"
            fill="white">Panic</text
          >

          <!-- Node 4: Patch (bottom left) -->
          <circle
            cx="130"
            cy="360"
            r="50"
            fill="#78716c"
            stroke="#57534e"
            stroke-width="2"></circle>
          <text
            x="130"
            y="365"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="14"
            font-weight="bold"
            fill="white">Patch</text
          >

          <!-- Node 5: Repeat (top left) -->
          <circle
            cx="100"
            cy="160"
            r="50"
            fill="#78716c"
            stroke="#57534e"
            stroke-width="2"></circle>
          <text
            x="100"
            y="165"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="14"
            font-weight="bold"
            fill="white">Repeat</text
          >

          <!-- Arrows -->
          <defs>
            <marker
              id="decay-arrow"
              markerWidth="10"
              markerHeight="10"
              refX="9"
              refY="3"
              orient="auto"
            >
              <polygon points="0 0, 10 3, 0 6" fill="#57534e"></polygon>
            </marker>
          </defs>

          <!-- Ship to Complain -->
          <path
            d="M 290 95 Q 340 110 360 135"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#57534e"
            stroke-width="2"
            marker-end="url(#decay-arrow)"></path>

          <!-- Complain to Panic -->
          <path
            d="M 395 210 Q 390 280 380 310"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#57534e"
            stroke-width="2"
            marker-end="url(#decay-arrow)"></path>

          <!-- Panic to Patch -->
          <path
            d="M 320 375 Q 250 400 180 375"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#57534e"
            stroke-width="2"
            marker-end="url(#decay-arrow)"></path>

          <!-- Patch to Repeat -->
          <path
            d="M 120 310 Q 105 280 105 210"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#57534e"
            stroke-width="2"
            marker-end="url(#decay-arrow)"></path>

          <!-- Repeat to Ship -->
          <path
            d="M 140 135 Q 175 105 210 90"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#57534e"
            stroke-width="2"
            marker-end="url(#decay-arrow)"></path>
        </svg>

        <!-- Dark Mode SVG -->
        <svg
          width="500"
          height="500"
          viewBox="0 0 500 500"
          class="max-w-full h-auto hidden dark:block"
        >
          <!-- Center circle -->
          <circle
            cx="250"
            cy="250"
            r="55"
            fill="#1c1917"
            stroke="#a8a29e"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-dasharray="4 2"></circle>
          <text
            x="250"
            y="245"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="12"
            fill="#a8a29e">Performance</text
          >
          <text
            x="250"
            y="260"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="12"
            fill="#a8a29e">Decay</text
          >

          <!-- Node 1: Ship (top) -->
          <circle
            cx="250"
            cy="70"
            r="50"
            fill="#a8a29e"
            stroke="#78716c"
            stroke-width="2"></circle>
          <text
            x="250"
            y="75"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="14"
            font-weight="bold"
            fill="#1c1917">Ship</text
          >

          <!-- Node 2: Complain (top right) -->
          <circle
            cx="400"
            cy="160"
            r="50"
            fill="#a8a29e"
            stroke="#78716c"
            stroke-width="2"></circle>
          <text
            x="400"
            y="165"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="14"
            font-weight="bold"
            fill="#1c1917">Complain</text
          >

          <!-- Node 3: Panic (bottom right) -->
          <circle
            cx="370"
            cy="360"
            r="50"
            fill="#a8a29e"
            stroke="#78716c"
            stroke-width="2"></circle>
          <text
            x="370"
            y="365"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="14"
            font-weight="bold"
            fill="#1c1917">Panic</text
          >

          <!-- Node 4: Patch (bottom left) -->
          <circle
            cx="130"
            cy="360"
            r="50"
            fill="#a8a29e"
            stroke="#78716c"
            stroke-width="2"></circle>
          <text
            x="130"
            y="365"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="14"
            font-weight="bold"
            fill="#1c1917">Patch</text
          >

          <!-- Node 5: Repeat (top left) -->
          <circle
            cx="100"
            cy="160"
            r="50"
            fill="#a8a29e"
            stroke="#78716c"
            stroke-width="2"></circle>
          <text
            x="100"
            y="165"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="14"
            font-weight="bold"
            fill="#1c1917">Repeat</text
          >

          <!-- Arrows -->
          <defs>
            <marker
              id="decay-arrow-dark"
              markerWidth="10"
              markerHeight="10"
              refX="9"
              refY="3"
              orient="auto"
            >
              <polygon points="0 0, 10 3, 0 6" fill="#a8a29e"></polygon>
            </marker>
          </defs>

          <!-- Ship to Complain -->
          <path
            d="M 290 95 Q 340 110 360 135"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#a8a29e"
            stroke-width="2"
            marker-end="url(#decay-arrow-dark)"></path>

          <!-- Complain to Panic -->
          <path
            d="M 395 210 Q 390 280 380 310"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#a8a29e"
            stroke-width="2"
            marker-end="url(#decay-arrow-dark)"></path>

          <!-- Panic to Patch -->
          <path
            d="M 320 375 Q 250 400 180 375"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#a8a29e"
            stroke-width="2"
            marker-end="url(#decay-arrow-dark)"></path>

          <!-- Patch to Repeat -->
          <path
            d="M 120 310 Q 105 280 105 210"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#a8a29e"
            stroke-width="2"
            marker-end="url(#decay-arrow-dark)"></path>

          <!-- Repeat to Ship -->
          <path
            d="M 140 135 Q 175 105 210 90"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#a8a29e"
            stroke-width="2"
            marker-end="url(#decay-arrow-dark)"></path>
        </svg>
      </div>

      <!-- The Steps -->
      <h2
        class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-8 mt-16"
      >
        The Five Stages
      </h2>

      <ol
        class="space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-stone-800 dark:text-stone-200 mb-12"
      >
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span
            class="flex-shrink-0 font-display text-3xl font-bold text-stone-400 dark:text-stone-500"
            >1</span
          >
          <div>
            <span class="font-semibold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100"
              >Ship features quickly.</span
            >
            <p class="mt-2 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">
              The team moves fast, delivering new functionality. Performance
              considerations take a back seat to feature velocity. Technical
              debt accumulates quietly.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span
            class="flex-shrink-0 font-display text-3xl font-bold text-stone-400 dark:text-stone-500"
            >2</span
          >
          <div>
            <span class="font-semibold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100"
              >Users complain about slow or broken experiences.</span
            >
            <p class="mt-2 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">
              Support tickets arrive. Metrics dashboards turn red. Users start
              leaving for competitors. The accumulated debt becomes visible.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span
            class="flex-shrink-0 font-display text-3xl font-bold text-stone-400 dark:text-stone-500"
            >3</span
          >
          <div>
            <span class="font-semibold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100"
              >Teams panic and patch symptoms.</span
            >
            <p class="mt-2 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">
              Emergency fixes. All-hands firefighting. Quick patches that
              address symptoms without touching root causes. The codebase grows
              more complex.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span
            class="flex-shrink-0 font-display text-3xl font-bold text-stone-400 dark:text-stone-500"
            >4</span
          >
          <div>
            <span class="font-semibold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100"
              >Performance improves temporarily.</span
            >
            <p class="mt-2 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">
              The immediate crisis passes. Dashboards stabilize. Leadership
              breathes a sigh of relief. The team returns to shipping features.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span
            class="flex-shrink-0 font-display text-3xl font-bold text-stone-400 dark:text-stone-500"
            >5</span
          >
          <div>
            <span class="font-semibold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100"
              >The cycle repeats as complexity grows.</span
            >
            <p class="mt-2 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">
              Each iteration leaves the system slightly more fragile. The time
              between crises shortens. The patches become less effective. The
              cycle accelerates.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <!-- Breaking the Cycle -->
      <div
        class="my-16 py-8 border-t-2 border-b-2 border-stone-300 dark:border-stone-600"
      >
        <h2
          class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-6"
        >
          Breaking the Cycle
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-stone-800 dark:text-stone-200">
          Fast by Default replaces this reactive loop with a disciplined,
          repeatable system where performance improves as part of normal work
          rather than emergency work. Instead of treating speed as something to
          fix later, it becomes a natural outcome of how the team builds
          software every day.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Call to Action -->
      <div class="text-center mt-12">
        <a
          href="/"
          class="inline-block px-8 py-4 bg-stone-900 dark:bg-stone-100 text-white dark:text-stone-900 font-sans font-semibold text-base tracking-wide uppercase hover:bg-stone-700 dark:hover:bg-stone-300 transition-colors"
        >
          Learn the Fast by Default Method
        </a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
